column5: How the heck do you fish in this?
This is what i'm doing this morning... http://www.kalassa.net/propilkki2/index.php?eng=1
with a parka? man its chilli out...fells like it could ("S" word inserted here ) out

we went anyways.froze our butts off, caught a few perch,not enough to make a meals, so let em go. the best part of this time of the years is no water skiers and seadoos !!!!!!!!! The wind was bitter and the water is 57 at the surface. Caught more fish on the games on wfn.com. http://www.wfn.tv/contest/games/fishclaw/  BTW i fish 5 min from my house in the Laprairie basin of the st lawerence seaway near Montreal.Just in case you wanted to look.
pretty sure I saw some of those things a few minutes ago driving home from brunch

Dress up nice & warm with rain gear on or a survival suit and a way you go, we were on the Bay of Quinte yesterday doing 60 + MPH in Bass boats & caught a nice number of Lmbass but not big enough, ended up with 11.92 lbs for 5 fish my biggest was 3lbs, we had a limit at 10:30 & culled up after that, nice Green weeds in 4' to 7' of water, 62 degree water, Texas rigged a Bassmagnet Tubes & a small Tungsten weight, should have wore my Survival suit but left it on shore, just a little cool Richard
